Vitamins
Vitamins can be either watersoluble or lipidsoluble Fat soluble vitamins are absorbed in the same manner as
lipids It is important to consume some amount of dietary lipid to aid the absorption of lipidsoluble vitamins
Watersoluble vitamins can be directly absorbed into the bloodstream from the intestine
